products.name: Jerry Stepman
products.text:
Jerry Stepman
5.0 out of 5 stars
 Feels Good
Reviewed in Canada on February 26, 2018
Verified Purchase
Abus have a very good reputation and that doesn't change with this lock. Great for the gym of whatever you need a solid padlock for. I trust this much more than a Master Lock or any other of the big names. I might be 10$, but you don't have to worry about your valuables when you leave. The bar also aligns towards the hole with a magnet or something, nice extra touch. Smooth internals, no jamming.

products.name: Repeat Customer Grapevine
products.text:
Repeat Customer Grapevine
5.0 out of 5 stars
 Please thumb up my review...
Reviewed in the United States on July 18, 2024
Verified Purchase
I shopped alot of products so you won't have to. People are finding faults with all these locks, like easy to pick or opens with a hammer hit..
If there was one perfect lock all the other companies would be out of business, so obviously, there is no perfect lock. This one will not secretly change the combo over night and it will not rust in a month.
It's an economic answer to your worries, so buy it. It works fine and is very strong.

products.name: Z. Cherry
products.text:
Z. Cherry
4.0 out of 5 stars
 Classic lock. Fun to pick, better than most Master Locks. Not for high-security use.
Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2024
Verified Purchase
Takes about a minute to pick, but its a solid lock, but has some security pins, so the average person probably couldn't rake it in a few seconds like a Master Lock #1-5.

Good cheap lock that would work for a gym locker if you don't keep anything very valuable in it, like a wallet, purse or watches.

For those, I'd go up to something like an American Lock 1100 or something with more security spool and serrated pins. Or really a disk detainer lock, because most people wouldn't have the tools or skill to pick them quickly enough to not get caught.

Report
